his [link](https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/keras/custom_callback)."],"metadata":{"id":"X2BhUHn3CPDI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Remember to inherit from the correct class\n","class myCallback(tf.keras.callbacks.Callback):\n","  # Define the correct function signature for on_epoch_end\n","  def on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs={}):\n","    if (logs.get('accuracy') > 0.99):\n","      print(\"\\nReached 99% accuracy so cancelling training!\") \n","\n","      # Stop training once the above condition is met\n","      self.model.stop_training = True"],"metadata":{"id":"DSOOhUUPCRop","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1660257789930,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":273,"user":{"displayName":"Erkam Sis","userId":"12927304356672166161"}}},"execution_count":14,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Create and train your model\n","\n","Now that you have defined your callback it is time to complete the `train_mnist` function below. \n","\n","**You must set your model to train for 10 epochs and the callback should fire before the 9th epoch for you to pass this assignment.**\n","\n","**Hint:**\n","- Feel free to try the architecture for the neural network that you see fit but in case you need extra help you can check out an architecture that works pretty well at the end of this notebook."],"metadata":{"id":"qooTgfZLCVmp"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["def train_mnist(x_train, y_train):\n","\n","  # Instantiate the callback class\n","  callbacks = myCallback()\n","\n","  # Define the model\n","  model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),\n","                                    tf.keras.layers.Dense(512, activation=tf.nn.relu),\n","                                    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation=tf.nn.softmax)]) \n","  # Compile the model\n","  model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n","                loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', \n","                metrics=['accuracy']) \n","  # Fit the model for 10 epochs adding the callbacks\n","  # and save the training history\n","  history = model.fit(x_train, y_train, epochs=10, callbacks=[callbacks])\n","\n","  return history"],"metadata":{"id":"K8Tq7IQZCYKJ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1660257793127,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"Erkam Sis","userId":"12927304356672166161"}}},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Call the `train_mnist` passing in the appropiate parameters to get the training history:"],"metadata":{"id":"8qKmK-w7CavR"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["hist = train_mnist(x_train, y_train)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"bNlVEmPjCcmh","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1660257842301,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":46922,"user":{"displayName":"Erkam Sis","userId":"12927304356672166161"}},"outputId":"c067fea5-a838-4e12-e1c1-62ad0bb460c3"},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Epoch 1/10\n","1875/1875 [==============================] - 10s 5ms/step - loss: 0.2030 - accuracy: 0.9395\n","Epoch 2/10\n","1875/1875 [==============================] - 9s 5ms/step - loss: 0.0810 - accuracy: 0.9751\n","Epoch 3/10\n","1875/1875 [==============================] - 9s 5ms/step - loss: 0.0520 - accuracy: 0.9837\n","Epoch 4/10\n","1875/1875 [==============================] - 9s 5ms/step - loss: 0.0372 - accuracy: 0.9881\n","Epoch 5/10\n","1867/1875 [============================>.] - ETA: 0s - loss: 0.0276 - accuracy: 0.9907\n","Reached 99% accuracy so cancelling training!\n","1875/1875 [==============================] - 10s 5ms/step - loss: 0.0276 - accuracy: 0.9907\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["If you see the message `Reached 99% accuracy so cancelling training!` printed out after less than 9 epochs it means your callback worked as expected. "],"metadata":{"id":"oE_rULyICeo8"}}]}
